      "message": "Potential Logic Issue with Readonly User Setup (Lines 547-549)\nSeverity: Medium File: gui/gui_test/overview_menu/test_overview_menu.robot Line: 547-549\n\nIssue: The keyword includes logic to create a readonly user, but the test case \"Verify Asset Tag Update With Readonly User\" already has [Setup] Create Readonly User And Login To GUI in its setup (Line 436). This creates redundant user creation.\n\nWhy: Redundant user creation causes several problems:\n\nPerformance: Creating users twice unnecessarily slows down test execution\nPotential Conflicts: Attempting to create the same user twice may cause errors or unexpected behavior\nMaintenance Burden: Two places to update if user creation logic changes\nCode Clarity: Unclear which creation is actually needed, confusing for future maintainers\nTest Reliability: If the first creation succeeds but second fails (or vice versa), test behavior becomes unpredictable\nBest Practice Violation: DRY (Don\u0027t Repeat Yourself) principle - setup logic should be in one place\nCurrent Code:\n\n    # Setup for readonly user.\n    IF  \u0027${user_type}\u0027 \u003d\u003d \u0027readonly\u0027\n       Create Readonly User And Login To GUI\n    END\n\nRecommendation: Remove the redundant user creation from the keyword since it\u0027s already handled in the test case setup:\n\n    # Note: Readonly user setup is handled by test case [Setup] when needed\nOr alternatively, remove the [Setup] from the test case and rely solely on the keyword\u0027s logic.",
