      "side": 1,
      "message": "Potential Race Condition (Line 552)\nSeverity: Low File: gui/gui_test/overview_menu/test_overview_menu.robot Line: 552\n\nIssue: Using Wait AND Click Element without verifying the element is clickable could lead to flaky tests.\n\nWhy: Waiting only for element visibility doesn\u0027t guarantee clickability, which can cause:\n\nFlaky Tests: Element might be visible but disabled, covered by another element, or still animating\nFalse Failures: Tests fail intermittently in CI/CD pipelines due to timing issues\nDebugging Difficulty: Race conditions are hard to reproduce and diagnose\nCI/CD Instability: Flaky tests reduce confidence in the test suite and slow down development\nBest Practice: Selenium/Robot Framework best practices recommend explicit wait for clickability\nReal-World Scenarios:\nButton might be visible but disabled during page load\nModal overlays or loading spinners might cover the button\nCSS animations might make button temporarily unclickable\n\n\nCurrent Code:\n\n    Wait AND Click Element  ${xpath_asset_tag_edit_button}\n\n\nRecommendation: Add explicit wait for element to be clickable:\n\n    Wait Until Element Is Enabled  ${xpath_asset_tag_edit_button}  timeout\u003d10\n    Click Element  ${xpath_asset_tag_edit_button}",
