      "message": "Variable Naming Inconsistency and Deprecated Keyword (Lines 555-556)\nSeverity: Medium File: gui/gui_test/overview_menu/test_overview_menu.robot Line: 555-556\n\nIssue: Two problems: (1) The variable ${new_hostname} is misleading because it\u0027s being used for asset tag, not hostname. (2) Using deprecated Set Variable keyword instead of modern VAR syntax.\n\nWhy:\n\nMisleading variable names cause significant problems:\n\nConfusion: Developers reading the code will expect hostname operations, not asset tag operations\nMaintenance Errors: Future changes to hostname logic might accidentally modify asset tag logic (or vice versa)\nDebugging Difficulty: When tests fail, misleading names make it harder to identify the actual problem\nCopy-Paste Errors: This suggests the code was copied from hostname-related tests without proper adaptation\nSemantic Mismatch: The test is about asset tags, but variables reference hostname - creates cognitive dissonance\nUsing deprecated Set Variable is problematic:\n\nSet Variable is deprecated since Robot Framework 7.0 (Robocop: DEPR05)\nModern VAR syntax is more concise, readable, and maintainable\nDeprecated keywords will eventually be removed from Robot Framework\nUsing deprecated syntax makes code harder to maintain and update\nVAR syntax is the recommended approach in all new code\nCurrent Code:\n\n    ${overview_hostname}\u003d  Get Text  ${xpath_hostname}\n    ${new_hostname}\u003d  Set Variable  ${overview_hostname}_new\n    \nRecommendation: Use accurate variable names AND modern VAR syntax:\n\n    ${current_asset_tag}\u003d  Get Text  ${xpath_hostname}\n    VAR    ${new_asset_tag}    ${current_asset_tag}_new",
