      "message": "Inconsistent Indentation in IF Block (Lines 562-570)\nSeverity: Medium File: gui/gui_test/overview_menu/test_overview_menu.robot Line: 562-570\n\nIssue: The indentation inside the nested IF blocks is inconsistent. Line 560 has incorrect indentation.\n\nWhy: Consistent indentation is critical in Robot Framework because:\n\nIt defines the logical structure and scope of control flow statements\nInconsistent indentation makes code harder to read and maintain\nIt can lead to confusion about which statements belong to which block\nRobot Framework style guide recommends 4 spaces per indentation level\nMixed indentation (6 spaces vs 7 spaces) suggests copy-paste errors or manual editing mistakes\nAutomated tools (robocop, robot.tidy) will flag this as a style violation\n\nCurrent Code:\n\n    IF  \u0027${action}\u0027 \u003d\u003d \u0027save\u0027\n      Click Element  ${xpath_asset_tag_save_button}\n       IF  \u0027${user_type}\u0027 \u003d\u003d \u0027readonly\u0027\n          Verify Error And Unauthorized Message On GUI\n       ELSE\n          Verify Success Message On BMC GUI Page\n       END\n       Page Should Not Contain  ${xpath_asset_tag_save_button}\n       Element Should Contain  ${xpath_asset_tag} ${new_hostname}\n\nProblem: Line 563 uses 6 spaces, while lines 564-570 use 7 spaces. This creates inconsistent indentation levels.\n\nRecommendation: Use consistent indentation (4 spaces per level):\n\n    IF  \u0027${action}\u0027 \u003d\u003d \u0027save\u0027\n        Click Element  ${xpath_asset_tag_save_button}\n        IF  \u0027${user_type}\u0027 \u003d\u003d \u0027readonly\u0027\n            Verify Error And Unauthorized Message On GUI\n        ELSE\n            Verify Success Message On BMC GUI Page\n        END\n        Page Should Not Contain  ${xpath_asset_tag_save_button}\n        Element Should Contain  ${xpath_asset_tag}  ${new_hostname}",
